          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12674609/comment/13799964",
            "id": "13799964",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=vinodkv",
              "name": "vinodkv",
              "key": "vinodkv",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Vinod Kumar Vavilapalli",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Asia/Kolkata"
            },
            "body": "bq. Are there current applications that want to write in parallel to multiple local disks?\nClearly MR. I'm sure others do too.\n\nbq. If not, then we should probably figure out how to support them well when they show up.\nWe cannot break MR.\n\nbq. In the meanwhile, we could look at the above mentioned drawbacks and decide whether the they are worth fixing or not, either by restricting solution above or some other solution. Are the above drawbacks worthwhile issues? If yes, are there alternative proposals for a solution?\nI just gave a solution above that may just work: \"And the better solution for that is to make apps ask the number of disks to write when they launch containers. That way YARN isn't overriding users intention to use/not use multiple disks.\"\n\nIf that solution sounds fine, we can run with it, thinking more about disk resources in general.\n",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=vinodkv",
              "name": "vinodkv",
              "key": "vinodkv",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Vinod Kumar Vavilapalli",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Asia/Kolkata"
            },
            "created": "2013-10-19T18:12:12.109+0000",
            "updated": "2013-10-19T18:12:12.109+0000"
          },
          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12674609/comment/13799970",
            "id": "13799970",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=bikassaha",
              "name": "bikassaha",
              "key": "bikassaha",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=bikassaha&avatarId=29845",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=bikassaha&avatarId=29845",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=bikassaha&avatarId=29845",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=bikassaha&avatarId=29845"
              },
              "displayName": "Bikas Saha",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
            },
            "body": "When does MR use multiple disks in the same task/container? Isnt the map output written to a single indexed partition file?\n\nRequiring apps to specify the number of disks for a container is also a viable solution and can be done in a back-compatible manner by changing MR to specify multiple disks and leaving the default to 1 for apps that dont care.",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=bikassaha",
              "name": "bikassaha",
              "key": "bikassaha",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=bikassaha&avatarId=29845",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=bikassaha&avatarId=29845",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=bikassaha&avatarId=29845",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=bikassaha&avatarId=29845"
              },
              "displayName": "Bikas Saha",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
            },
            "created": "2013-10-19T18:42:00.004+0000",
            "updated": "2013-10-19T18:42:00.004+0000"
          },
          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12674609/comment/13809885",
            "id": "13809885",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=cdouglas",
              "name": "cdouglas",
              "key": "chris.douglas",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Christopher Douglas",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
            },
            "body": "bq. When does MR use multiple disks in the same task/container? Isnt the map output written to a single indexed partition file?\n\nSpills are spread across all volumes, but merged into a single file at the end.\n\nWould randomizing the order of disks be a reasonable short-term workaround for (1)? Future changes could weight/elide directories based on other criteria, but that's a simple change. So would changing the \"random\" selection to bias its search order using a hash of the task id (instead of disk usage when creating the spill), so the ShuffleHandler could search fewer directories on average. I agree with Vinod, it would be hard to prevent the search altogether...\n\nbq. Requiring apps to specify the number of disks for a container is also a viable solution and can be done in a back-compatible manner by changing MR to specify multiple disks and leaving the default to 1 for apps that dont care.\n\nThis makes sense as a hint, but some users might interpret it as a constraint and be confused when a NM schedules them on a node the reports fewer local dirs (due to failure, heterogeneous config).",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=cdouglas",
              "name": "cdouglas",
              "key": "chris.douglas",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Christopher Douglas",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
            },
            "created": "2013-10-31T03:14:58.421+0000",
            "updated": "2013-10-31T03:14:58.421+0000"
          },
          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12674609/comment/13810228",
            "id": "13810228",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jlowe",
              "name": "jlowe",
              "key": "jlowe",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Jason Darrell Lowe",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "America/Chicago"
            },
            "body": "+1 for randomizing the list of directories.  Even if we allow an app to ask for multiple paths and they do so, it's more likely to spread the load around for apps with unsophisticated load balancing algorithms.",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jlowe",
              "name": "jlowe",
              "key": "jlowe",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
