      {
        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12674609/comment/13809885",
        "id": "13809885",
        "author": {
          "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=cdouglas",
          "name": "cdouglas",
          "key": "chris.douglas",
          "avatarUrls": {
            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
          },
          "displayName": "Christopher Douglas",
          "active": true,
          "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
        },
        "body": "bq. When does MR use multiple disks in the same task/container? Isnt the map output written to a single indexed partition file?\n\nSpills are spread across all volumes, but merged into a single file at the end.\n\nWould randomizing the order of disks be a reasonable short-term workaround for (1)? Future changes could weight/elide directories based on other criteria, but that's a simple change. So would changing the \"random\" selection to bias its search order using a hash of the task id (instead of disk usage when creating the spill), so the ShuffleHandler could search fewer directories on average. I agree with Vinod, it would be hard to prevent the search altogether...\n\nbq. Requiring apps to specify the number of disks for a container is also a viable solution and can be done in a back-compatible manner by changing MR to specify multiple disks and leaving the default to 1 for apps that dont care.\n\nThis makes sense as a hint, but some users might interpret it as a constraint and be confused when a NM schedules them on a node the reports fewer local dirs (due to failure, heterogeneous config).",
        "updateAuthor": {
          "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=cdouglas",
          "name": "cdouglas",
          "key": "chris.douglas",
          "avatarUrls": {
            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
